# Instructions for coding agents

This is **{{.Name}}**, an application built on the [hex](https://github.com/jordanbrauer/hex)
Go framework. This file is the fast path for AI coding agents working in this
repository. The authoritative, always-current reference is the hex manpages:

- `man hex` — the CLI and its generators (**hex**(1))
- `man 7 hex` — the framework conventions: layout, markers, provider lifecycle
- `man 5 hex` — the config file formats (TOML, env map, CUE schema)
- `man 3 hex` — the embedded Lua module API

## Generate, don't hand-author

Prefer the `hex` generators over writing files by hand. They place code in the
canonical location, apply the naming conventions, and **auto-wire** it into the
app — the parts that are easy to get wrong. Preview any generator with
`--dry-run` (add `--format json` for machine-readable output) before committing.

- `hex make provider <name>` — a service provider, wired into `app/boot.go`
- `hex make domain <name>` — a domain package (entity, repository port, service, errors)
{{- if .HasDatabase}}
- `hex make migration <name>` — a timestamped SQL migration pair
- `hex make adapter <domain>` — a SQL adapter implementing a domain repository
{{- end}}
- `hex make command <name>` — a Cobra command, wired into `app/command/root.go`
{{- if .Web}}
- `hex make controller <name>` — an HTTP controller, wired into `app/provider/routes.go`
{{- end}}

Run `hex make:<cmd> --help` for the full flag set, or `man hex` for all of them.

## Layout

- `app/` — wiring: `boot.go` (provider order), `provider/`, `command/`{{if .Web}}, `controller/`{{end}}
- `domain/` — business logic; depends on nothing outside itself
- `infrastructure/` — adapters implementing domain ports
- `config/` — TOML config, `schema.cue`, env map (see `man 5 hex`)
{{- if .HasDatabase}}
- `database/` — migrations
{{- end}}

## Marker comments — never remove them

The generators wire new code by inserting above marker comments. Keep each one
on its own line:

- `// hex:providers` in `app/boot.go`
- `// hex:commands` in `app/command/root.go`
{{- if .Web}}
- `// hex:routes` in `app/provider/routes.go`
{{- end}}
- `// hex:repl` in `app/provider/repl_bindings.go`

## Verify your changes

```
just check        # fmt-check{{ if .Lint }} + lint{{ end }} + vet + race tests
{{- if .Web}}
go run . serve    # boot the app and exercise it
{{- end}}
go test ./...     # unit + end-to-end (webtest) tests
```
